# Vercel Environment Variables for Token Exchange (Swap)
# =======================================================
#
# This is what makes the swap work exactly like https://elementswap-eta.vercel.app/
#
# The working demo uses Circle App Kit with the key set correctly as NEXT_PUBLIC_KIT_KEY.
# Only this name is inlined into the browser bundle at build time.
#
# STEPS (do these exactly):
# 1. Go to https://vercel.com/siribraheems-projects/arcpay-web-app/settings/environment-variables
# 2. Click "Import" or "Add New".
# 3. Name (exact): NEXT_PUBLIC_KIT_KEY
# 4. Value (exact, use the one you have): KIT_KEY:6cf763f8e10487acad829a36e7e5f100:a8b0df17de46b4a981548ea76ae37b0d
# 5. Type: Plain text (not encrypted)
# 6. Targets: Check Production, Preview, and Development
# 7. Save/Import.
#
# 8. CRITICAL: Go to the Deployments tab.
# 9. Find the latest production deployment.
# 10. Click the ... menu on it > Redeploy.
#
# After the new deployment is READY, the swap in your dashboard (Token Exchange panel) will work the same as the demo site.
#
# Do NOT use KIT_KEY or CIRCLE_KIT_KEY alone - they won't be available in the client code.
# After setting, always redeploy so the value is baked into the build.
#
# The code in this repo is now aligned with the working demo (strict NEXT_PUBLIC_KIT_KEY, correct minimal swap params, non-blocking estimate, fresh adapter, gas check, chain switch).

NEXT_PUBLIC_KIT_KEY=KIT_KEY:your-id:your-secret-here

# Optional Privy:
# NEXT_PUBLIC_PRIVY_APP_ID=your-privy-id
